content:
Learn how Financial Services Cloud can help your business and customers. Understand its core functionality, create a trial org, and learn how to get started.

Retail Banking: By using Financial Services Cloud for Retail Banking, bankers get a 360-degree view of their customers including customer profile, interests, life goals, and events, as well as financial accounts.

Wealth Management: Financial advisors can use the Wealth Management Lightning app for a complete view of their customers and to deliver personalized service. Advisors can deepen client relationships, personalize engagements, and increase productivity.

Insurance: The Insurance Agent Console app helps agents track performance and stay focused on goals. The distributor performance dashboard provides sales managers with a consolidated performance summary for all distributors.

Onboarding: The Discovery Framework feature lets you create assessment questions, surface digital assessments, and collect information for onboarding customers.

Mortgage: Mortgage for Financial Services Cloud includes a new data model for mortgage applications, standard flow templates, and flow screen components.

Commercial Banking: The Commercial Banking Console app gives bankers greater visibility into customer relationships in commercial lending, treasury management, trade finance, and more.
title: Getting Started with Financial Services Cloud
